From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v32 - msleep(500) at bridge_enable for DP TX settle

After v31 (remove bridge_disable) bridge programming runs cleanly but
HDMI signal still doesn't lock to GPU output (backlight off).  Theory:
bridge_enable runs immediately after GPU's encoder_commit (DPMS_ON ->
setup_dig_transmitter ENABLE).  DP signal needs to stabilize before
MN864729 can lock onto it.  cq_wait_set steps for DP lane status
(0x60f8/0x60f9) silently no-op on unstable signal.

Add 500ms msleep at start of bridge_enable.  Also #include linux/delay.h.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@
 
 #include <linux/i2c.h>
 #include <linux/i2c-algo-bit.h>
+#include <linux/delay.h>
 
 
 #include "amdgpu.h"
@@ -393,6 +394,9 @@
 		return;
 	}
 
+	/* v32: 500ms settle for GPU DP TX before bridge tries to lock */
+	msleep(500);
+
 	if(pdev->vendor != PCI_VENDOR_ID_ATI) {
 		DRM_ERROR("Invalid vendor: %04x", pdev->vendor);
 		return;
